{{Infobox artist | name = Ako Castuera | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | birth_date = | birth_place = | nationality = American | spouse = | field = Animation, Ceramics, Paintings | training = | alma_mater = [[California College of the Arts]] | works = | awards = | website = {{URL|http://thinging.wordpress.com/}} }} '''Ako Castuera''' is an American artist who is best known for being a writer and storyboard artist on the animated television series ''[[Adventure Time]]''.
==Early life== Castuera's father is from Mexico, and his ancestors originated from the [[Spain|Spanish]] city [[Castuera]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Castuera|first1=Ako|title=About|url=http://thinging.wordpress.com/about/|publisher=[[WordPress]]|accessdate=October 3, 2014|date=2009}}</ref> Her mother is of [[Okinawa]]n descent.<ref>Castuera, Ako (Storyboard artist). 2014. "Return to the Nightosphere" [Commentary track], ''Adventure Time'' Season Four [DVD], Los Angeles, CA: [[Cartoon Network]].</ref> According to an article published by the [[Smithsonian Asian Pacific American Center]], she was "born at home in a [[commune]] to non-hippy parents."<ref>{{cite web|title=Art Intersections|url=http://apa.si.edu/asianlatino/art.html|publisher=[[Smithsonian Asian Pacific American Center|apa.si.edu]]|accessdate=October 3, 2014}}</ref>
==History== Castuera graduated from the [[California College of the Arts]], and it was at this university that she got involved with ''[[Giant Robot (magazine)|Giant Robot]]'', a bi-monthly magazine of [[Asian people|Asian]] and [[Asian American]] [[pop culture|popular culture]]. After graduating, she moved to Los Angeles and eventually landed a job as a character designer on the [[Adult Swim]] series ''[[Metalocalypse]]'' after she drew a card for the series' lead character designer, [[Songgu Kwon]]. After an indie comic of hers was well received by [[Pendleton Ward]], she was hired as a storyboard revisionist on the Cartoon Network series ''[[Adventure Time]]''.<ref name=ccainterview>{{cite web|last1=Tedford|first1=Matthew|title=Ako Castuera: Giant Robots, Mangled Corpses, and Magical Dogs|url=https://www.cca.edu/news/2013/09/18/ako-castuera-giant-robots-mangled-corpses-and-magical-dogs|publisher=[[California College of the Arts|CCA.edu]]|accessdate=October 3, 2014|date=September 18, 2013}}</ref> She was eventually promoted to storyboard artist, and served in that position until she left in 2013 to focus fully on her art career.<ref name=ccainterview/><ref name=tumblr>{{cite web|last=''Adventure Time'' staff|title=Billy’s Bucket List Promo by Writer/Storyboard Artist Ako Castuera|url=http://kingofooo.tumblr.com/post/79784443956/billys-bucket-list-promo-by-writer-storyboard|work=King of Ooo|publisher=[[Tumblr]]|accessdate=April 25, 2014|date=March 16, 2014}}</ref> In October 2014, however, she returned to the series to temporarily storyboard several episodes during the show's [[Adventure Time (season 7)|seventh season]],<ref>{{cite web|last1=Osborne|first1=Kent|title=[Osborne, revealing Moynihan and Castuera are partners for season 7]|url=http://instagram.com/p/tiY9F8DW8y/?modal=true|publisher=[[Instagram]]|accessdate=September 29, 2014|date=September 29, 2014}}</ref> and during the show's [[Adventure Time (season 8)|eighth season]], worked as a storyboard revisionist.
